Helen

All Greece
  entreats you,
    to remember
  the apples,
  laid bare,
  on the boughs,
  fragile to touch,
     yet too golden,
     too ripe.

Is there a way to wait,
when the sun
  is lingering slow
    in the dew’s biting mirage?

Is it her majesty,
  she waits,
  she waits too.

H.D.

- HD
